t%3B%20before%20his%20death%20at%20the%20age%20of%2065.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fshane-macgowans-wife-says-singer-was-determined-to-live-only-a-few-days-ago-13022852%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Behind%20Congress%20Defeat%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20a%20Clear%20Rejection%20of%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20Leadership%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04183801%2F395318885_880178123664508_4838573835910956742_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBhopal%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20historic%20mandate%20for%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20assembly%20election%20hardly%20requires%20overanalysing.%20Succinctly%2C%20it%20is%20a%20comprehensive%20rejection%20of%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20The%20state%20Congress%20chief%E2%80%99s%20hubristic%20conduct%20of%20electioneering%20antagonised%20a%20large%20section%20of%20the%20electorate%20enough%20to%20forgive%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20omissions%20and%20commissions%20as%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20age%20was%20already%20an%20apparent%20disadvantage%20for%20the%20septuagenarian%20Congress%20warhorse%3B%20he%20exacerbated%20the%20disadvantage%20with%20a%20series%20of%20peremptory%20decisions%20that%20helped%20the%20BJP%20overcome%20initial%20nervousness%20and%20return%20to%20the%20fight%20with%20a%20bang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20start%20with%2C%20he%20marginalised%20all%20other%20state%20leaders%20except%20Digvijaya%20Singh%3B%20his%20gratuitous%20decision%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20BJP%20on%20Hindutva%20was%20another%20strategic%20blunder%3B%20he%20contemptuously%20rejected%20offers%20of%20INDIA%20partners%20such%20as%20Samajwadi%20Party%20and%20Aam%20Adami%20Party%20(AAP)%20on%20seat%20adjustments%20and%20provided%20ammo%20to%20the%20BJP%20to%20deride%20the%20%E2%80%9CCongress%20culture%E2%80%9D%20of%20factionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArguably%2C%20his%20most%20self-destructive%20stance%20was%20to%20smugly%20repeat%20the%20refrain%20before%20the%20media%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20the%20people%2C%20not%20the%20Congress%20that%20are%20fighting%20the%20election%20against%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20misgovernance%E2%80%9D.%20Whatever%20he%20meant%20by%20this%2C%20the%20voters%20interpreted%20the%20assessment%20as%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20weakness%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20aggressive%20campaign.%20Simply%20put%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20CM%20face%20offered%20victory%20on%20a%20platter%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Kamal%20Nath%20frittered%20away%20opportunity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamal%20Nath%20frittered%20away%20the%20opportunity%20to%20avenge%20the%20toppling%20of%20his%2015-month-old%20government%20in%20March%202020%20by%20the%20BJP%20in%20collusion%20with%20Congress%20rebel%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20widespread%20belief%20until%20three%20months%20ago%20that%20the%20Congress%20looked%20all%20set%20to%20return%20to%20power%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20with%20a%20bigger%20mandate%20than%20in%202018.%20The%20party%20was%20euphoric%20over%20its%20spectacular%20victory%20in%20Karnataka.%20Taking%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20book%2C%20it%20coined%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmadhya-pradesh-scams-bjp-congress-paras-saklecha%5C%22%3E50%25%20commission%20%3Cem%3Eki%20sarkar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20to%20emphasise%20corruption%20in%20the%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20government.%20The%20slogan%20resonated%20with%20the%20people.%20Also%2C%20a%20bouquet%20of%20freebies%20that%20helped%20the%20Congress%20win%20the%20southern%20state%20was%20promised%20for%20MP%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20decisions%2C%20taken%20in%20quick%20succession%2C%20had%20apparently%20unnerved%20the%20ruling%20party.%20The%20BJP%20central%20leadership%20betrayed%20its%20nervousness%20in%20the%20decision%20to%20take%20command%20of%20the%20campaign%2C%20denying%20Chouhan%20the%20role%20of%20the%20spearhead%20that%20he%20was%20allowed%20to%20play%20in%20the%20previous%20three%20assembly%20elections.%20The%20election%20was%20fought%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20image.%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20photograph%20was%20among%20a%20group%20of%20ten%20state%20leaders%20beneath%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20much%20larger%20one%20in%20party%20hoardings%20and%20banners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20an%20opportune%20time%20for%20the%20Congress%20to%20capitalise%20on%20the%20confusion%20in%20the%20BJP%20over%20its%20chief%20ministerial%20face.%20But%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20insipid%20leadership%20was%20not%20up%20to%20the%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26210023%2FF6uAo6VbgAAYzDa.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221117%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26210023%2FF6uAo6VbgAAYzDa.jpeg%201117w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26210023%2FF6uAo6VbgAAYzDa-300x157.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26210023%2FF6uAo6VbgAAYzDa-1024x534.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677021%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22583%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40ChouhanShivraj%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShivraj%E2%80%99s%20bounce-back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20enough%2C%20the%20BJP%20made%20a%20course%20correction%20and%20brought%20Chouhan%20to%20the%20centre%20stage%20of%20the%20campaign%2C%20short%20of%20declaring%20him%20the%20chief%20ministerial%20candidate.%20Charged%20with%20the%20restoration%20of%20his%20authority%2C%20Chouhan%20hit%20the%20campaign%20trail%20with%20renewed%20vigour.%20He%20covered%20164%20out%20of%20230%20constituencies.%20He%20regaled%20the%20audiences%2C%20particularly%20women%2C%20with%20his%20characteristic%20histrionics%20interspersed%20with%20emotional%20rhetoric.%20He%20was%20back%20in%20action%20with%20full%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20bounce-back%20with%20panache%20in%20the%20poll%20arena%20should%20have%20alarmed%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20but%20their%20rather%20jaded%20speeches%20%E2%80%93%20in%20far%20fewer%20constituencies%20than%20Chouhan%20covered%20%E2%80%93%20ensured%20the%20gradual%20dwindling%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20prospects.%20While%20Chouhan%20was%20unstoppable%2C%20the%20Congress%20sorely%20lacked%20resources%20to%20match%20his%20drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20mainly%20depended%20on%20rallies%20of%20its%20star%20campaigners%20such%20as%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20Rahul%20and%20Priyanka%20Gandhi-Vadra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20BJP%20marshalled%20its%20resources%20%E2%80%93%20both%20monetary%20and%20human%20%E2%80%93%20to%20an%20unprecedented%20scale.%20While%20the%20chief%20minister%20crisscrossed%20the%20state%2C%20central%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20including%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20%E2%80%93%20kept%20the%20tempo%20of%20the%20BJP%20campaign%20on%20a%20high%20pitch%20through%20their%20whirlwind%20tours%20in%20electorally%20strategic%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmadhya-pradesh-election-shivraj-singh-chouhan%5C%22%3EFor%20BJP%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20a%20Leap%20in%20Seats%2C%20a%20Jump%20in%20Vote%20Share%20and%20a%20Reversal%20of%202018%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommunication%20deficit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20far%20fewer%20election%20rallies%20resulted%20in%20its%20promises%20reaching%20far%20fewer%20voters%20than%20the%20BJP.%20Kamal%20Nath%20addressed%20the%20most%20number%20of%20rallies%20from%20the%20Congress%20but%20his%20age%20circumscribed%20his%20outreach.%20Next%20to%20him%20was%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20but%20age%20took%20a%20toll%20on%20his%20schedule%20too.%20Although%20far%20more%20sprightly%20for%20his%20age%20than%20Kamal%20Nath%2C%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20march%20the%20pace%20of%20much%20younger%20Chouhan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20Congress%20leaders%20were%20barely%20visible%20on%20the%20ground.%20It%20was%20no%20surprise%20then%20that%20the%20party%20failed%20to%20effectively%20communicate%20its%20promises%20and%20programmes%20to%20a%20large%20section%20of%20the%20voters%2C%20be%20it%20caste-based%20census%2C%20free%20education%20or%20subsidised%20gas%20cylinders.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmadhya-pradesh-election-shivraj-singh-chouhan%5C%22%3ELadli%20Behna%20Yojana%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20immensely%20popular%20across%20the%20state%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20tours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20had%20generously%20delegated%20responsibilities%20to%20the%20second%20and%20third%20line%20of%20leaders%2C%20the%20Congress%20would%20have%20fared%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAged%20Jai-Veeru%20pair%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAICC%20general%20secretary%20in%20charge%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20had%20dubbed%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20as%20Jai%20and%20Veeru%20from%20the%20legendary%20%3Cem%3ESholay%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1975)%20film%2C%20presumably%20to%20emphasise%20their%20friendship%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20the%20electorate%20interpreted%20Surjewala%E2%80%99s%20statements%20as%20Nath%20and%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20age%20being%20closer%20to%20the%20present%20ages%20of%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20and%20Dharmendra%2C%20who%20had%20essayed%20the%20memorable%20roles%20of%20the%20two%20small-time%20burglar-friends%20in%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20analysts%20are%20attributing%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20stunning%20victory%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20to%20mainly%20two%20factor%3A%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20vigorous%20campaigning%20and%20chief%20minister%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20Ladli%20Behna%20Yojana.%20The%20analysis%20is%20true%20but%20only%20partly%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20crucial%20two%20factors%20that%20led%20to%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20crushing%20defeat%20in%20the%20election%20were%20ideological%20overlapping%20on%20Hindutva%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20projection%20of%20its%20two-man%20gerontocracy%20%E2%80%93%20Kamal%20Nath%20(77)%20and%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20(76)%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20harbinger%20of%20change.%20Although%20he%20had%20ruled%20as%20chief%20minister%20for%2018%20years%2C%20Chouhan%20(64)%20still%20exuded%20youthfulness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamal%20Nath%20and%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20tightly%20supervised%20and%20executed%20most%20election-related%20decisions%20in%20the%20state%20Congress%2C%20leaving%20little%20room%20for%20interference%20from%20the%20younger%20lot.%20Acutely%20conscious%20of%20the%20duo%E2%80%99s%20clout%20in%20the%20high%20command%2C%20all%20others%20fell%20in%20line%20with%20their%20diktats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123530%2FThe-Wire-43-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123530%2FThe-Wire-43-1.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123530%2FThe-Wire-43-1-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123530%2FThe-Wire-43-1-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680772%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20leaders%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%20and%20Kamal%20Nath%20during%20a%20public%20meeting%20in%20Mandla%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20on%20October%2012%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20X(Twitter)%2F%40priyankagandhi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeremptory%20decision%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamal%20Nath%20peremptorily%20picked%20up%20candidates%2C%20citing%20internal%20party%20surveys%20that%20no%20others%20%E2%80%93%20except%20possibly%20Singh%20%E2%80%93%20had%20any%20clue%20about.%20When%20seat%20distribution%20triggered%20revolts%20in%20a%20dozen%20constituencies%2C%20Nath%20yielded%20to%20change%20candidates%20in%20some%20places%20but%20not%20before%20kicking%20up%20an%20unsavoury%20controversy.%20His%20infamous%20%E2%80%9Ctear%20Digvijaya%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20clothes%E2%80%9D%20jibe%20was%20provoked%20by%20a%20demonstration%20of%20the%20supporters%20of%20a%20candidate%20who%20was%20denied%20the%20ticket.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20Singh%20tauntingly%20responded%20to%20the%20jibe.%20The%20controversial%20banter%20in%20an%20open%20meeting%20between%20the%20two%20veterans%20gave%20ammo%20to%20the%20BJP%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fnation%2Fpolitics%2F091123%2Fmy-govt-made-4-cr-pucca-houses-for-poor-but-i-havent-made-one-for-mys.html%5C%22%3Ederide%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekapda%20fad%3C%2Fem%3E%20(tearing%20clothes)%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamal%20Nath%20contemptuously%20rejected%20proposals%20for%20seat%20adjustment%20with%20INDIA%20partners.%20His%20curt%20%E2%80%9CAkhilesh-Vakhilesh%E2%80%9D%20remark%20must%20still%20be%20ringing%20in%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20supremo%E2%80%99s%20ears.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20PCC%20chief%20had%20announced%20the%20cancellation%20of%20INDIA%E2%80%99s%20first%20public%20meeting%20that%20was%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20in%20Bhopal%2C%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20central%20observers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20it%20was%20Kamal%20Nath%20who%20unilaterally%20decided%20to%20pit%20the%20Congress%20against%20the%20BJP%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmadhya-pradesh-in-quest-for-power-is-congress-ready-to-compromise-on-secularism%5C%22%3Ecompetitive%20display%20of%20religiosity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Digvijaya%20Singh%2C%20whose%20antipathy%20to%20Hindutva%20is%20well%20known%2C%20grudgingly%20surrendered%20to%20the%20PCC%20chief%E2%80%99s%20ploy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20results%20show%2C%20all%20the%20strategies%20that%20Kamal%20Nath%20sounded%20so%20confident%20about%20ahead%20of%20the%20election%20miserably%20flopped.%20The%20BJP%2C%20which%20looked%20vulnerable%20on%20account%20of%20its%2018-year%20rule%2C%20got%20its%20acts%20together%20with%20remarkable%20swiftness%20and%20scored%20a%20historic%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20road%20ahead%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20road%20ahead%20for%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Digvijay%20Singh%20has%20virtually%20hit%20the%20cul-de-sac.%20While%20Kamal%20Nath%20can%20save%20face%20in%20his%20victory%20and%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20sweep%20in%20all%20seven%20seats%20in%20Chhindwara%2C%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20was%20not%20that%20lucky.%20his%20brother%20Laxman%20Singh%20lost%20the%20election%20and%20son%20Jaivardhan%20Singh%20barely%20scraped%20through%20in%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20Raghogarh%20seat.%20Singh%20Senior%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20term%20is%20due%20to%20expire%20in%202026%20and%20by%20that%20time%20he%20will%20turn%2079.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20the%20election%20is%20over%2C%20muted%20voices%20in%20the%20party%20are%20bound%20to%20find%20expression.%20Earlier%2C%20such%20voices%20had%20arisen%20in%20March%202020%2C%20when%20the%20veterans%20had%20failed%20to%20prevent%20the%20revolt%20by%20Scindia%20that%20toppled%20the%20Congress%20government.%20But%20the%20high%20command%20ignored%20the%20pleas%20for%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20resignation.%20Far%20from%20it%2C%20the%20Gandhis%20chose%20to%20give%20virtually%20untrammelled%20power%20to%20their%20family%20acolyte.%20The%20same%20blunder%20could%20be%20suicidal%20for%20any%20chance%20of%20revival%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20Five%20months%20from%20now%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20is%20due%20and%20the%20Congress%20has%20another%20opportunity%20to%20take%20on%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20election%20has%20also%20taught%20a%20useful%20lesson%20to%20the%20Congress%20if%20it%20cares%20to%20learn%3A%20playing%20the%20Hindutva%20card%20on%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20pitch%20is%20a%20recipe%20for%20disaster.%20Nath%20declared%20himself%20as%20a%20Hanuman-%3Cem%3Ebhakt%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20courted%20controversial%20religious%20preachers%20such%20as%20Dhirendra%20Shastri%20and%20Pt%20Pradeep%20Mishra.%20Both%20openly%20advocate%20the%20establishment%20of%20Hindu%20Rashtra.%20Kamal%20Nath%20had%20no%20ideological%20qualms%20in%20organising%20their%20%3Cem%3Ekathas%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Chhindwara.%20Taking%20a%20cue%20from%20him%2C%20many%20other%20Congress%20candidates%20also%20invited%20Shastri%20and%20Mishra%20to%20conduct%20discourses%20in%20their%20respective%20constituencies.%20The%20end%20result%20of%20the%20dalliance%20with%20Hindutva%20politics%20proved%20deleterious%20for%20the%20Congress.%20It%20did%20not%20earn%20a%20victory%20for%20the%20Congress%20candidates%20but%20perhaps%20raised%20doubts%20among%20potential%20voters%20about%20its%20secular%20credentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701695814000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F