xed%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Cem%3ENewsweek%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%20The%20report%20is%20based%20on%20the%20remarks%20made%20by%20Andrey%20Gurulyov%2C%20a%20Russian%20Parliament%20(Duma)%20member%20and%20former%20military%20commander.%20An%20excerpt%20of%20Mr%20Gurulyov's%20comments%2C%20made%20during%20an%20appearance%20on%20Russian%20state%20television%20channel%20Russia-1%2C%20were%20widely%20circulated%20on%20Telegram.%20SMERSH%20was%20created%20by%20the%201940s%20by%20Joseph%20Stalin.%20It%20is%20an%20acronym%20of%20Russian%20words%20that%20mean%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20to%20spies%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20talked%20about%20SMERSH%2C%20today%20we%20created%20a%20department%20that%20works%20in%20approximately%20the%20same%20way%20in%20new%20territories%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Gurulyov%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20regions%20of%20Donetsk%2C%20Luhansk%2C%20Kherson%20and%20Zaporizhzhia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20areas%20are%20under%20illegal%20occupation%20of%20Russia%20after%20a%202022%20referendum.%20Many%20western%20countries%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Unites%20States%2C%20have%20called%20the%20move%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20government%20has%20not%20made%20any%20comment%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organisation%20was%20originally%20focussed%20on%20combating%20German%20spies%20infiltrating%20the%20Soviet%20military.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fwhat-smersh-russia-ukraine-stalin-1849136%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENewsweek%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20SMERSH%20was%20operational%20till%201946%2C%20and%20was%20infamous%20for%20the%20arrest%2C%20torture%20and%20execution%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20including%20any%20its%20own%20agents%20suspected%20of%20sabotage%2C%20desertion%20or%20disloyalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gurulyov%20said%20a%20similar%20structure%20should%20also%20operate%20once%20again%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20interfere%20with%20our%20operations%20in%20non-frontline%20areas.%20I%20talked%20to%20the%20Far%20East%2C%20where%20we%20have%20nuclear%20submarines%20and%20where%20our%20ships%20are%20based.%20They%20may%20also%20be%20in%20danger%2C%20so%20we%20need%20to%20approach%20protection%20issues%20a%20little%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Russian%20politician%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20website%20of%20Kharkiv%20Human%20Rights%20Protection%20Group%20said%20those%20caught%20by%20SMERSH%20operatives%20are%20tortured%20into%20providing%20videoed%20%26quot%3Bconfessions%20and%20apologies%26quot%3B%20merely%20for%20displaying%20a%20Ukrainian%20flag%2C%20other%20Ukrainian%20symbols%20or%20singing%20Ukraine's%20national%20anthem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%20shows%20no%20sign%20of%20slowing.%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20forces%20continue%20to%20fight%20in%20Ukraine's%20east%20and%20the%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Ukrainian%20officials%20said%20that%20Russian%20forces%20are%20assaulting%20the%20industrial%20town%20of%20Avdiivka%20in%20the%20east%20from%20two%20new%20directions%2C%20as%20Moscow%20expands%20its%20bid%20to%20capture%20the%20almost%20encircled%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%20has%20been%20trying%20for%20nearly%20two%20months%20to%20seize%20Avdiivka%2C%20an%20industrial%20town%20in%20the%20eastern%20Donetsk%20region%20that%20has%20become%20the%20fiercest%20flashpoint%20on%20the%20sprawling%20frontline.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701692280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2F69hc674_vladimir-putin-reuters_625x300_06_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsmersh-russia-revives-soviet-era-spy-hunting-squads-in-ukraine-report-4632949%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SMERSH%20was%20created%20by%20the%201940s%20by%20Joseph%20Stalin.%20It%20is%20an%20acronym%20of%20Russian%20words%20that%20mean%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20to%20spies%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22enga