ible%20to%20get%20through%20the%20assistant%20and%20the%20coordinator%20steps%20to%20get%20to%20that%20prestigious%20manager%20title%2C%26quot%3B%20James%2C%20who%20is%20now%2030%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20just%20such%20a%20genuine%20excitement%20for%20it%20that%20getting%20to%20manager%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20like%2C%20'oh%20my%20gosh%2C%20I've%20made%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20reached%20her%20goal%20and%20became%20a%20marketing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboss-management-leadership-advice-hiring-developing-people-earning-respect-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emanager%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2026.%20However%2C%20the%20position%20came%20with%20new%20responsibilities%20and%20concerns.%20She%20questioned%20if%20she%20had%20the%20skills%20and%20experience%20to%20help%20her%20reports%20grow%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20a%20manager%20to%20me%20is%20very%20important%20to%20ensure%20you%20can%20assist%20your%20team%20with%20their%20own%20development%20and%20their%20career%20trajectory%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20at%2026%20I%20was%20navigating%20my%20own%20career%20trajectory%20whilst%20trying%20to%20help%20others%20with%20theirs%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20recalled%20feeling%20%26quot%3Bcrippling%20anxiety%20of%20imposter%20syndrome%26quot%3B%20at%20a%20leadership%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'oh%20my%20God%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20find%20out%20that%20I'm%20just%20young%20and%2026%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20I'm%20doing%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20ended%20up%20leaving%20that%20manager%20role.%20She%20said%20it%20was%20just%20too%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-and-gen-z-dont-want-to-be-managers-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eearly%20in%20her%20career%20to%20be%20a%20manager%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20said%20at%2026%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20don't%20know%20yourself%2C%20and%20there's%20still%20so%20much%20to%20learn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20she%20is%20a%20manager%20at%20another%20company%20and%20believes%20she%20can%20help%20her%20predominantly%20Gen%20Z%20team%20with%20their%20hard%20and%20soft%20skills%20and%20share%20what%20she%20learned%20when%20she%20was%20in%20her%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20creates%20job-related%20content%20on%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40kimelizabethjames1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETikTok%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20account.%20Becoming%20a%20people%20manager%20was%20one%20of%20the%20things%20on%20James'%20list%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40kimelizabethjames1%2Fvideo%2F7301128106021113096%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETikTok%20video%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20career-related%20things%20she%20wouldn't%20do%20again%20in%20her%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20wants%20to%20be%20a%20manager%20at%20all.%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20talked%20to%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-no-promotion-manager-stress-pay-work-life-balance-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emillennials%20who%20prefer%20being%20individual%20contributors%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20don't%20see%20the%20pressure%20the%20role%20can%20come%20with%20as%20worth%20it.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visier.com%2Fblog%2Fnew-research-individual-contributors-shun-management%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EVisier%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20only%2038%25%20of%20individual%20contributors%20were%20interested%20in%20being%20a%20people%20manager%20where%20they%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBeing%20a%20manager%20in%20her%2020s%20versus%20her%2030s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20James%20was%20a%20manager%20in%20her%2020s%2C%20she%20worried%20about%20having%20the%20time%20to%20keep%20her%20skills%20up%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20what%20led%20her%20%26quot%3Bto%20reaching%20full-on%20career%20burnout%26quot%3B%20at%2028.%20She%20said%20the%20pandemic%20had%20an%20impact%20too%20and%20noted%20she%20%26quot%3Bwas%20trying%20to%20do%20it%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20trying%20to%20manage%20and%20give%20to%20my%20people%2C%20but%20then%20also%20my%20own%20abilities%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20eight%20years%20at%20the%20company%2C%20she%20felt%20burned%20out.%20She%20also%20wanted%20to%20branch%20out%20because%20she%20had%20been%20at%20the%20same%20company%20since%20university%20graduation.%20She%20took%20a%20consulting%20job%20and%20was%20able%20to%20focus%20on%20her%20skills.%20She%20noted%20it%20%26quot%3Bwas%20the%20perfect%20reset.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20able%20to%20just%20have%20a%20level%20of%20service%20that%20I%20could%20provide%20to%20my%20clients%2C%20and%20it%20just%20brought%20me%20back%20to%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20during%20that%20time%20my%20confidence%20in%20myself%20and%20my%20own%20abilities%20just%20skyrocketed.%20And%20that's%20when%20I%20started%20to%20think%20with%20time%20and%20also%20starting%20to%20hit%2030%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20why%20did%20I%20want%20to%20become%20a%20people%20manager%20so%20badly%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20said%20she%20wished%20someone%20told%20her%20being%20a%20manager%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20have%20to%20be%20the%20only%20kind%20of%20attribution%20to%20success%26quot%3B%20and%20instead%20figuring%20out%20ways%20to%20develop%20and%20expand%20her%20skills%20or%20work%20on%20larger%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20is%20now%20chief%20customer%20officer%20where%20she%20said%20she%20loves%20coaching%20her%20team%20and%20helping%20them%20with%20their%20development%2C%20such%20as%20with%20learning%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enew%20skills%20and%20ca