ZPM)%20is%20poised%20for%20a%20massive%20victory%20over%20its%20regional%20rival%2C%20the%20Mizo%20National%20Front%20(MNF).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20website%2C%20ZPM%20won%2027%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20comfortably%20more%20than%20the%20simple%20majority%20mark%20of%2021%20in%20the%2040-member%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20has%20made%20the%20ZPM%E2%80%99s%20victory%20sweeter%20is%20also%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20Lalthansanga%20defeating%20chief%20minister%20and%20MNF%20supremo%20Zoramthanga%20by%202%2C101%20votes%20in%20the%20Aizawl%20East-1%20seat.%20MNF%20looks%20set%20to%20win%2010%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%20won%202.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%20is%20set%20to%20win%20only%20one%20seat%2C%20the%20Lawngtlai%20West%20seat%20%E2%80%93%20its%20worst%20performance%20in%20recent%20years%20in%20the%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVoting%20for%20the%20elections%20in%20the%20Northeastern%20state%20was%20held%20in%20a%20single%20phase%20on%20November%207.%20Over%2080%25%20of%20the%20electorate%20participated%20in%20the%20ballot%20that%20saw%20174%20candidates%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20including%2016%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20ECI%20had%20set%20December%203%20as%20the%20date%20for%20the%20counting%20of%20votes%2C%20like%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20four%20states%20that%20voted%20in%20November%2C%20the%20poll%20body%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fec-changes-counting-date-for-mizoram-assembly-polls-to-december-4%5C%22%3Erevise%20the%20date%20to%20December%204%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20poll%20panel%20received%20multiple%20representations%20from%20political%20parties%2C%20the%20Church%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%20as%20December%203%20was%20a%20Sunday%2C%20the%20holy%20day%20for%20Christians%2C%20a%20majority%20in%20the%20state.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%E2%80%99s%20win%20in%20three%20North%20Indian%20states%20and%20the%20Congress%20taking%20Telangana%20on%20December%203%20has%20already%20set%20the%20tone%20in%20the%20media%20for%20election-related%20deliberations%20and%20stock-taking%2C%20the%20sweep%20of%20ZPM%20in%20a%20tiny%20state%20like%20Mizoram%20is%20also%20noteworthy.%20Here%20are%20eight%20takeaways%20from%20today%E2%80%99s%20Mizoram%20electoral%20results.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20ZPM%E2%80%99s%20win%20means%20Mizoram%20will%20get%20a%20new%20face%20as%20its%20chief%20minister%20in%20Lalduhoma.%20It%20can%20also%20mean%2079-year-old%20Zoramthanga%2C%20a%20stalwart%20in%20Mizo%20politics%20for%20over%20three%20decades%2C%20sailing%20off%20into%20the%20political%20sunset.%20Already%2C%20another%20veteran%20Mizo%20politician%2C%20former%20two-time%20chief%20minister%20Lalthanhawla%2C%20had%20announced%20his%20retirement%20from%20politics%20after%20the%202018%20loss%20of%20his%20Congress%20party.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Today%E2%80%99s%20gigantic%20win%20by%20ZPM%20has%20also%20changed%20the%2035-year-old%20cycle%20of%20MNF%20and%20Congress%20sharing%20power%20in%20the%20border%20state%20alternately.%20After%20the%20signing%20of%20the%20Mizo%20Accord%20with%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%20in%201986%2C%20the%20Congress%20government%20under%20Lalthanhawla%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20post%20to%20give%20way%20to%20MNF%E2%80%99s%20Laldenga.%20Since%20then%2C%20in%20every%20assembly%20poll%2C%20the%20national%20party%20has%20been%20engaged%20in%20a%20two-corner%20contest%20with%20the%20MNF%20until%20the%20ZPM%20arrived%20on%20the%20scene%20in%20the%202018%20polls%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20upped%20its%20game%20under%20Narendra%20Modi.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20With%20the%20MNF%20failing%20to%20repeat%20its%202018%20win%20in%20the%20state%2C%20the%20regional%20party%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20break%20the%20cycle%20in%20Mizoram%20of%20a%20party%20failing%20to%20return%20to%20power%20for%20a%20third%20consecutive%20term.%20It%20is%20no%20cakewalk%20for%20any%20party%20to%20sidestep%20anti-incumbency%20and%20return%20to%20power%20for%20a%20third%20term.%20In%20the%20Northeast%2C%20only%20the%20Congress%20under%20the%20chief%20ministership%20of%20Tarun%20Gogoi%20could%20pull%20it%20off%20in%20Assam%20in%202011.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29124850%2FF05qfKDacAAHNnr.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29124850%2FF05qfKDacAAHNnr.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29124850%2FF05qfKDacAAHNnr-300x151.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29124850%2FF05qfKDacAAHNnr-1024x514.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29124850%2FF05qfKDacAAHNnr-800x400.jpeg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677473%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22602%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMizoram%20chief%20minister%20Zoramthanga.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%20%2F%40ZoramthangaCM%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20December%204%20election%20results%20that%20threw%20up%20two%20wins%20for%20the%20BJP%20have%20underlined%20that%20its%20footprint%20in%20Mizoram%20is%20growing.%20However%2C%20it%20also%20holds%20up%20that%2C%20once%20again%2C%20the%20national%20party%20failed%20to%20have%20an%20MLA%20in%20the%20state%20from%20the%20majority%20Mizo%20community.%20This%20was%20even%20after%20the%20assembly%20speaker%20from%20the%20MNF%2C%20Lalrinliana%2C%20had%20shifted%20base%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20these%20elections.%20This%20makes%20Mizoram%20the%20only%20state%20where%20BJP%20has%20failed%20to%20enter%20a%20north-eastern%20state%E2%80%99s%20majority%20community%20in%20spite%20of%20being%20in%20power%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20In%20all%2C%20the%20BJP%20contested%2023%20seats.%20Only%20five%20of%20its%20candidates%20were%20non-Mizos.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Today%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20has%20also%20shown%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Mara%20community%20has%20further%20firmed%20up.%20While%20the%20party%20candidate%20K.%20Hrahmo%20won%20the%20Palak%20seat%2C%20K.%20Beichhua%2C%20a%20former%20senior%20minister%20of%20the%20MNF%20who%20also%20recently%20moved%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20picked%20up%20the%20Siaha%20seat%20for%20the%20party.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20two%20wins%20for%20the%20BJP%20came%20soon%20after%20its%20sweep%20of%20the%20Mara%20District%20Council%20in%20Mizoram.%20In%202017%2C%20the%20Mara%20Democratic%20Front%20merged%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20gave%20the%20national%20party%20a%20much-needed%20entry%20into%20the%20Mara%20community%2C%20the%20second%20most%20influential%20community%20after%20the%20Mizos.%20In%202019%2C%20that%20move%20helped%20the%20BJP%20grab%20the%20Mara%20District%20Council.%20This%20past%20April%2C%20the%20BJP%20swept%20the%20Council%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20BJP%20losing%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcan-the-bjp-emerge-as-kingmaker-in-mizoram-as-pollsters-predict-a-hung-assembly%5C%22%3ETuichawng%20constituency%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20hold%20in%202018%20over%20the%20Chakma%20community%20in%20Mizoram%20was%20most%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20popularity%20of%20its%20then-candidate%20Budha%20Dhan%20Chakma.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBudha%20Dhan%20Chakma%2C%20a%20former%20minister%20in%20the%20Lalthanhawla%20government%2C%20had%20moved%20to%20the%20BJP%20close%20to%20the%202018%20elections%20and%20went%20on%20to%20give%20the%20party%20its%20first%20taste%20of%20victory%20in%20Mizoram%E2%80%99s%20assembly%20elections.%20This%20time%20around%2C%20Budha%20Dhan%20had%20announced%20his%20retirement%20from%20politics%2C%20leading%20the%20BJP%20to%20bank%20on%20a%20new%20candidate%2C%20Durjya%C2%A0%20Dhan%20Chakma.%20He%20lost%20to%20MNF%E2%80%99s%20Rasik%20Mohan%20Chakma.%20Like%20in%20the%20Mara%20Council%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20also%20succeeded%20in%20capturing%20the%20Chakma%20District%20Council%20of%20Mizoram%2C%20a%20strategy%20it%20had%20adopted%20some%20years%20ago%20to%20enter%20the%20Mizoram%20election%20fray.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20recent%20polls%2C%20today%E2%80%99s%20winner%20from%20the%20MNF%2C%20Rasik%20Mohan%20Chakma%2C%20became%20its%20chief%20executive%20member.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20MNF%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20power%20also%20means%20that%20the%20Mizos%20did%20not%20consider%20the%20ethnic%20strife%20in%20Manipur%20that%20had%20affected%20their%20kindred%20community%2C%20the%20Kukis%2C%20as%20an%20election%20issue.%20The%20voters%20rather%20bit%20into%20the%20ZPM%E2%80%99s%20stand%20during%20the%20campaigning%20that%20the%20Manipur%20issue%20is%20important%20to%20all%20Zo%20people%20and%20their%20politicians%20across%20party%20lines.%20Though%20Zoramthanga%20had%20stridently%20batted%20for%20the%20Kukis%2C%20and%20also%20for%20the%20displaced%20Chins%20of%20Myanmar%2C%20and%20tried%20tilting%20it%20into%20an%20election%20issue%2C%20the%20voters%20didn%E2%80%99t%20look%20at%20him%20as%20the%20only%20Mizo%20leader%20who%20can%20continue%20that%20support%20to%20their%20kindred%20lot.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Finally%2C%20while%20ZPM%E2%80%99s%20win%20has%20meant%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20new%20regional%20party%20in%20Mizoram%20after%20the%20MNF%2C%20the%20phenomenon%20is%2C%20but%2C%20only%20a%20second%20across%20the%20Northeast%20in%20recent%20times.%20In%20the%20last%20Nagaland%20elections%2C%20one%20saw%20a%20new%20regional%20party%2C%20the%20Nationalist%20Democratic%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(NDPP)%2C%20seizing%20power%20from%20an%20already%20entrenched%20regional%20entity%2C%20the%20Naga%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%20(NPF).%20Like%20the%20MNF%2C%20the%20NPF%20was%20also%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20first%20regional%20party%20to%20have%20grabbed%20power%20from%20the%20Congress%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20national%20party%20being%20well%20entrenched%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20in%20most%20of%20the%20Northeast.%20Like%20the%20MNF%2C%20the%20NPF%20was%20also%20a%20BJP%20ally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20NPF%2C%20ditto%20MNF%20in%20Mizoram%2C%20had%20resisted%20sharing%20power%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%20Nagaland%2C%20the%20NDPP%E2%80%99s%20win%20in%20Nagaland%20made%20way%20for%20the%20BJP%20to%20enter%20the%20state%20government%20not%20only%20for%20the%20first%20time%20but%20to%20also%20demand%20plum%20portfolios%20like%20that%20of%20the%20state%20home%20ministry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20even%20as%20counting%20was%20ongoing%20in%20Mizoram%2C%20the%20BJP%20state%20president%20Vanlalhmuaka%20told%20reporters%20that%20his%20party%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20participate%20in%20the%20new%20government%20which%20will%20be%20formed%20soon.%E2%80%9D%20Since%20the%20ZPM%20is%20seen%20as%20close%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20his%20statement%20could%20well%20be%20true.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20it%20does%2C%20it%20could%20be%20termed%20as%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20effective%20%E2%80%98Nagaland%20model%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20Christian-majority%20states%20in%20the%20Northeast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701679513000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04135901%2F401496004_762396555919280_8101576401723065424_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmizoram-eight-takeaways-zpm-mnf-bjp%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20has%20made%20the%20ZPM%E2%80%99s%20victory%20sweeter%20is%20also%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20Lalthansanga%20defeating%20chief%20minister%20and%20MNF%20supremo%20Zoramthanga%20by%202%2C101%20votes%20in%20the%20Aizawl%20East-1%20seat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmizoram-eight-takeaways-zpm-mnf-bjp%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Crimes%20Against%20Women%20and%20Children%2C%20Suicides%2C%20Sudden%20Deaths%20Increased%20in%202022%3A%20NCRB%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F18224008%2Fmax-kleinen-ugdKmhDg1m8-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(NCRB)%20released%20the%20annual%20crime%20report%2C%20and%20the%20Accidental%20Deaths%20and%20Suicides%20in%20India%20(ADSI)%20report%2C%20on%20Sunday%2C%C2%A0December%203%2C%20when%20the%20results%20of%20the%20Assembly%20elections%20in%20four%20states%20were%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20it%20was%20published%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fcrimes-against-women-children-scst-and-cyber-crimes-increased-in-2022-crime-in-india-report%2Farticle67602315.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20report%20provides%20a%20comprehensive%20overview%20of%20the%20crime%20scenario%20in%20India%20in%202022%2C%20including%20the%20number%20of%20sudden%20deaths%2C%20suicides%2C%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20children%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20crime%20rate%20declined%20from%207%25%20in%202021%20to%206.9%25%20in%202022%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported%2C%20citing%20the%20NCRB%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20crimes%20against%20specific%20categories%2C%20including%20women%2C%20children%2C%20SC%2C%20ST%2C%20and%20cyber%20crimes%2C%20increased%20compared%20to%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESudden%20deaths%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%2011.6%25%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20%E2%80%9Csudden%20deaths%E2%80%9D%20reported%20across%20the%20country%2C%20the%20ADSI%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2056%2C653%20sudden%20deaths%20were%20reported%20in%202022%2C%20with%20heart%20attacks%20accounting%20for%2032%2C410%20deaths.%20Other%20reasons%20were%20attributed%20for%2024%2C243%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20age%20group%20of%2045-60%20years%20reported%20the%20maximum%20number%20of%20deaths%20(19%2C456).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20study%20by%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%20and%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fmagazines%2Fpanache%2Fcardiovascular-diseases-killing-indians-the-most-pulmonary-embolism-rheumatic-condition-and-other-heart-disorders-people-should-know-about%2Farticleshow%2F94509483.cms%5C%22%3Eaccounts%20for%20approximately%2060%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20heart%20disease%20burden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuicides%20and%20accidental%20deaths%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuicides%20increased%20to%201%2C70%2C924%20in%202022%20compared%20to%201%2C64%2C033%20in%202021%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccidental%20deaths%20also%20increased%20to%204%2C30%2C504%20in%202022%20compared%20to%203%2C97%2C530%20in%202021%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fdata-gaps%2Fis-indias-highest-suicide-rate-because-of-better-reporting-or-rising-distress-836959%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FADSI-2021%2FADSI_2021_FULL_REPORT.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20highest%20suicide%20rate%20in%20its%20history%20in%202021%2C%20with%2012%20suicides%20for%20every%20100%2C000%20people.%20But%20the%20numbers%20could%20be%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20a%20psychiatrist%20had%20told%20%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20there%20are%20several%20reasons%20why%20India%20might%20be%20underreporting%20suicides.%20These%20are%20lack%20of%20medical%20certification%20of%20deaths%2C%20stigma%20associated%20with%20mental%20health%2C%20and%20criminalisation%2C%20not%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20reporting%20of%20sucides%20but%20sometimes%20also%20in%20the%20denial%20of%20insurance%20if%20the%20death%20is%20by%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECrimes%20against%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%204%2C45%2C256%20cases%20of%20%E2%80%98crimes%20against%20women%E2%80%99%20were%20registered%20in%202022%2C%20showing%20a%204%25%20increase%20from%202021%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajor%20cases%20included%20cruelty%20by%20husband%20or%20his%20relatives%2C%20kidnapping%20and%20abduction%20of%20women%2C%20assault%20on%20women%20with%20intent%20to%20outrage%20her%20modesty%2C%20and%20rape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-62830634%5C%22%3E2022%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%2C%20said%20that%20one%20in%20three%20women%20globally%20face%20gender-based%20violence%20and%20the%20numbers%20for%20India%20are%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20India%20recorded%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20crimes%20against%20women%20ever%20in%202021.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20rise%20of%2026.35%25%20over%20six%20years%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECrimes%20against%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%201%2C62%2C449%20cases%20of%20crimes%20against%20children%20were%20registered%20in%202022%2C%20reflecting%20an%208.7%25%20increase%20from%202021%2C%20the%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKidnapping%20and%20abduction%20and%20crimes%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20(POCSO)%20Act%20were%20prominent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20crimes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrimes%20against%20senior%20citizens%2C%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%2C%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%2C%20and%20economic%20offences%20showed%20a%20massive%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20total%20of%2028%2C545%20cases%20were%20registered%20for%20committing%20crimes%20against%20senior%20citizens%20(above%2060%20years)%2C%20showing%20an%20increase%20of%209.3%25%20over%202021%20(26%2C110%20cases)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20total%20of%2057%2C582%20cases%20were%20registered%20for%20committing%20crimes%20against%20SCs%2C%20showing%20an%20increase%20of%2013.1%25%20over%202021%20(50%2C900%20cases)%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20total%20of%2010%2C064%20cases%20were%20registered%20for%20committing%20crime%20against%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%2C%20showing%20an%20increase%20of%2014.3%25%20over%202021%20(8%2C802%20cases)%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%201%2C93%2C385%20cases%20were%20registered%20under%20economic%20offences%20%E2%80%93%20an%2011.1%25%20increase%20from%202021%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20cyber%20crimes%2C%2065%2C893%20cases%20were%20registered%2C%20showing%20a%2024.4%25%20increase%20in%20registration%20from%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%202022%2C%2064.8%25%20of%20the%20cyber%20crime%20cases%20registered%20were%20with%20the%20motive%20of%20fraud%20(42%2C710%20out%20of%2065%2C893%20cases)%20followed%20by%20extortion%20at%205.5%25%20(3%2C648%20cases)%2C%20and%20sexual%20exploitation%20at%205.2%25%20(3%2C434%20cases).%20A%20total%20of%205%2C610%20cases%20were%20registered%20in%202022%20as%20compared%20with%205%2C164%20cases%20in%20the%20year%202021%2C%20showing%20an%20increase%20of%208.6%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20daily%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%205%2C610%20cases%2C%2078.5%25%20of%20cases%20were%20registered%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Damage%20to%20Public%20Property%20Act%20(4%2C403%20Cases)%20followed%20by%201%2C005%20(17.9%25)%20cases%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701678620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F18224008%2Fmax-kleinen-ugdKmhDg1m8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcrimes-against-women-and-children-suicides-sudden-deaths-increased-in-2022-ncrb-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%204%2C45%2C256%20cases%20of%20'crimes%20against%20women'%20were%20registered%20in%202022%2C%20showing%20a%204%25%20increase%20from%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcrimes-against-women-and-children-suicides-sudden-deaths-increased-in-2022-ncrb-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK's%20only%20giant%20pandas%20leave%20after%2012%20years%20to%20return%20to%20China%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701678000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-giant-pandas-cages_6381927.jpg%3F20231204130133%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fedinburgh-zoos-giant-pandas-leave-their-home-of-12-years-to-start-journey-back-to-china-13022521%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Yang%20Guang%20and%20Tian%20Tian%20-the%20UK's%20only%20giant%20pandas%20-%20are%20leaving%20for%20China%20today%20after%20spending%2012%20years%20in%20Scotland.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fedinburgh-zoos-giant-pandas-leave-their-home-of-12-years-to-start-journey-back-to-china-13022521%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Verse%20Affairs%3A%20Annihilation%20Aesthetics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04122322%2FRH-Icelight.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ranjit%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20poem%20%E2%80%9CRetreat%E2%80%9D%2C%20included%20in%20his%20latest%20collection%20of%20poetry%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIcelight%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Penguin%2C%202023)%2C%20the%20dream%20of%20a%20sailor%20accommodates%20nostalgic%20yearnings%20with%20futuristic%20aspirations.%20Only%2015%20lines%20long%2C%20the%20poem%20compresses%20various%20striking%20images%20in%20five%20tercets%20or%20three-line%20stanzas.%20It%20begins%20dramatically%2C%20almost%20cinematically%2C%20with%20seawater%20withdrawing%20from%20the%20floor%20of%20a%20vessel%20and%20its%20admiral%20regaining%20his%20composure%20after%20being%20destabilised%20by%20a%20storm%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20floor%20is%20wet%20with%20the%20sea%E2%80%99s%20retreat%3Cbr%3E%5CnA%20draggled%20wing%3Cbr%3E%5Cndrapes%20its%20shadow%20on%20the%20bell%20tower%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20Admiral%2C%20your%20telescope!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20however%2C%20you%20realise%20that%20the%20images%20and%20voices%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20surreal.%20In%20a%20remarkable%20metaphor%2C%20Hoskote%20describes%20sleep%2C%20dreaming%2C%20but%20also%20time%3A%20%E2%80%9CHe%20scoops%20darkness%20%2F%20from%20darkness%E2%80%9D.%20If%20sleep%20and%20the%20subconscious%20are%20a%20vast%2C%20black%2C%20night-time%20sea%2C%20the%20sailor%20can%20be%20imagined%20to%20be%20rowing%20through%20it%20with%20his%20paddle%2C%20scooping%20up%20the%20dark%20waters%2C%20keeping%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENautical%20images%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20not%20uncommon%20in%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20poetry.%20In%20his%20earlier%20collection%20of%20poetry%2C%20%3Cem%3EJohanwhale%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2018)%2C%20he%20had%20drawn%20upon%20the%20Biblical%20Book%20of%20Jonah%2C%20Herman%20Melville%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMoby%20Dick%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1851)%2C%20and%20nautical%20histories%20to%20create%20elegies.%20His%20previous%20book%20of%20poetry%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHunchprose%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2021)%2C%20which%20I%20had%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fbeyond-business%2Fhunchprose-hoskote-s-poems-offer-a-bastion-of-truth-in-a-post-truth-world-121040901569_1.html%5C%22%3Ereviewed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20drew%20upon%20images%20of%20oceans%20and%20voyages%20as%20metaphors%20for%20narratives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%E2%80%9CRetreat%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20image%20of%20the%20sea%20is%20not%20only%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20subconscious%20but%20also%20a%20vessel%20that%20allows%20Hoskote%20to%20travel%20between%20genres%20of%20surreal%20and%20futuristic%20poetry.%20In%20the%20last%20two%20stanzas%20of%20the%20poem%2C%20it%20is%20revealed%20that%20the%20admiral%20of%20the%20ship%20is%20not%20travelling%20between%20two%20ports%20but%20between%20two%20worlds%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20surveyor%20continues%20to%20look%3Cbr%3E%5Cnfor%20a%20world%20at%20the%20other%20end%3Cbr%3E%5Cnof%20his%20spyglass%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eknowing%20it%E2%80%99s%20out%20there%3Cbr%3E%5Cna%20distant%20cousin%20to%20the%20one%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthat%E2%80%99s%20blowing%20up%20around%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20it%20is%20not%20too%20far-fetched%20to%20imagine%20that%20the%20vessel%20is%20an%20intergalactic%20spaceship%20with%20voyagers%20escaping%20from%20Earth%20torn%20apart%20by%20conflict%20and%20the%20disastrous%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%20There%20is%20an%20element%20of%20hope%2C%20of%20finding%20another%20planet%20that%20might%20accommodate%20humans%20when%20the%20third%20rock%20from%20the%20sun%20implodes%20because%20of%20our%20relentless%20activities.%20But%20it%20is%20also%20a%20grim%20image%2C%20of%20a%20world%20blowing%20up%20all%20around%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20as%20governments%20around%20the%20world%20have%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F11%2F1144127%5C%22%3Efailed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20act%20decisively%20to%20prevent%20climate%20change%20or%20stop%20conflict%20like%20the%20one%20roiling%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-israel-palestine-war-is-a-stain-on-every-one-of-us%5C%22%3EIsrael-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20October%207%2C%20annihilation%20anxiety%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F00030651030510020801%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20psychoanalysts%20as%20%E2%80%9C(f)ears%20of%20being%20overwhelmed%2C%20merged%2C%20penetrated%2C%20fragmented%2C%20and%20destroyed%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20has%20spiked.%20Polarisation%20around%20tentpole%20events%2C%20often%20acerbated%20by%20vicious%20online%20campaigns%2C%20only%20aggravates%20such%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHoskote%20has%20experienced%20the%20effects%20of%20such%20polarising%20himself%20following%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fcurator-ranjit-hoskote-resigns-from-documentas-finding-committee-over-anti-semitism-allegations%5C%22%3Eaccusations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20antisemitism%20in%20early%20November%20this%20year%20by%20the%20German%20daily%C2%A0%3Cem%3ES%C3%BCddeutsche%20Zeitung%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20signing%20a%202019%20BDS%20(Boycott%2C%20Disinvestment%20and%20Sanctions%20against%20Israel)%20petition%20against%20an%20event%20on%20%E2%80%9CZionism%20and%20Hindutva%E2%80%9D%20organised%20by%20the%20Consulate%20General%20of%20Israel%20in%20Mumbai.%20With%20the%20German%20government%20threatening%20to%20withdraw%20funding%20for%20Documenta%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20prestigious%20art%20exhibitions%20held%20every%20five%20years%20in%20Kassel%2C%20Germany%2C%20Hoskote%20resigned%20from%20the%20Finding%20Committee%20of%20its%20upcoming%2016th%20edition.%20In%20his%20resignation%20letter%2C%20he%20clarified%20his%20position%20that%20while%20he%20did%20not%20support%20the%20intellectual%20and%20cultural%20boycott%20of%20Israel%2C%20he%20was%20also%20opposed%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20any%20criticism%20of%20the%20country%20should%20be%20painted%20as%20%E2%80%9Cantisemitism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20dedicated%20my%20life%20to%20opposing%20authoritarian%20forces%20and%20discriminatory%20ideologies%2C%20and%20my%20signature%20carried%20with%20it%20the%20weight%20of%20my%20commitment%20to%20dialogue%2C%20inclusiveness%2C%20mutuality%2C%20and%20the%20ceaseless%20quest%20for%20common%20ground%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20letter.%20But%2C%20in%20this%20age%20of%20polarising%20debates%20augmented%20by%20social%20media%20algorithms%20and%20trigger-happy%20cancel%20culture%2C%20such%20nuance%20is%20easily%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHunchprose%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Hoskote%20had%20set%20up%20a%20dichotomy%20between%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20nuanced%20use%20of%20language%20and%20the%20shiny%20wordplay%20of%20a%20rhetorician.%20Anxiety%20about%20the%20utility%20of%20poetry%20in%20our%20world%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20ability%20to%20write%20it%20%E2%80%94%20informs%20some%20of%20the%20poems%20in%20his%20book%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRedacted%E2%80%9D%20is%20haunted%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20lost%20poem.%20It%20begins%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20poem%20was%20not%20found%20in%20his%20manuscripts%E2%80%9D.%20Then%2C%20a%20litany%20is%20provided%20of%20all%20the%20places%20where%20this%20poem%20is%20not%20found%3A%20%E2%80%9Cmanuscripts%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cconversations%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cinterviews%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Clectures%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Carchive%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Chard%20drives%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cxeroxes%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cindex%20cards%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20somewhat%20reminiscent%20of%20litanies%20and%20lists%20provided%20by%20the%20Chilean%20novelist%20Roberto%20Bola%C3%B1o%20in%20his%20byzantine%20novels%20about%20missing%20writers.%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20poem%20ends%20with%20the%20lines%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChased%20by%20prosecutors%20fanning%20their%20collars%3Cbr%3E%5Cnflashing%20across%20banners%20wayward%20as%20the%20wind%3Cbr%3E%5Cnnothing%20conclusive%20you%20understand%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthis%20poem%20may%20never%20be%20found%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20almost%20a%20nightmarish%20conclusion%20of%20silencing%2C%20of%20censorship%2C%20that%20might%20give%20sleepless%20nights%20to%20editors%2C%20literary%20scholars%2C%20and%20textual%20historians.%20How%20do%20you%20respond%20to%20a%20poem%20that%20is%20never%20found%3F%20What%20is%20the%20value%20of%20a%20lost%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20theme%20Hoskote%20returns%20to%20a%20little%20later%20in%20the%20book%2C%20in%20the%20poem%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Harappan%20Merchant%E2%80%99s%20Complaint%E2%80%9D.%20The%20titular%20merchant%20begins%20by%20demanding%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20do%20I%20care%20how%20these%20words%20sound%3Cbr%3E%5Cnin%20translation%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EJoppo%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekshumpa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eplaksha%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20detailed%20endnotes%20on%20this%20poem%2C%20Hoskote%20explains%20that%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejoppo%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0means%20water%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekshumpa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20mushroom%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eplaksha%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20fig%20tree.%20While%20the%20first%20one%20appears%20in%20Nihali%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20endangered%20Central%20Indian%20language%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20others%20are%20found%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ERig%20Veda%3C%2Fem%3E.%20All%20three%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20the%20language%20of%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20Civilisation%20that%20has%20eluded%20decipherment%20over%20the%20century%20since%20its%20discovery.%20Naturally%2C%20the%20Harappan%20merchant%20throws%20the%20gauntlet%20to%20the%20reader%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20decipher%20if%20you%20dare%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthese%20words%20sealed%20in%20images%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthe%20squat%20bull%20the%20sage%20lost%20in%20a%20trance%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ethe%20horned%20man%20fighting%20a%20tiger%3Cbr%3E%5CnAre%20these%20chants%20to%20cure%20the%20seasick%3Cbr%3E%5Cnor%20curses%20aimed%20at%20fleeing%20debtors%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20Harappan%20language%20is%20now%20lost%20to%20us%2C%20will%20our%20language%20also%20be%20lost%20to%20future%20generations%3F%20This%20anxiety%20is%20particularly%20poignant%20for%20someone%20like%20Hoskote%2C%20who%20is%20not%20only%20a%20poet%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIcelight%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20his%20eighth%20collection%20of%20poetry%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20an%20accomplished%20translator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%9CPaishachi%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20ghazal%20of%20sorts%2C%20refers%20to%20the%20legendary%20language%20of%20ghosts%20from%20which%20Kashmiri%20is%20said%20to%20have%20descended.%20All%20the%20couplets%20in%20this%20poem%20end%20with%20the%20refrain%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20language%20of%20ghosts%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20words%20sound%20like%20nothing%20that%20guests%20have%20ever%20spoken%20to%20hosts.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20is%20the%20language%20of%20my%20people%2C%20the%20language%20of%20living%20ghosts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20violence%20is%20not%20only%20epistemically%20experienced%3B%20it%20is%20also%20corporeal.%20The%20poem%20%E2%80%9CLesson%E2%80%9D%2C%20dedicated%20to%20Kashmiri%20poet%20and%20filmmaker%20Asiya%20Zahoor%2C%20also%20refers%20to%20the%20troubled%20region%20of%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20suppression%20of%20free%20speech.%20In%20the%20poem%2C%20a%20professor%20admonishes%20his%20class%2C%20asking%20them%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20to%20say%20a%20word%E2%80%9D.%20His%20chalk%20bifurcates%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20a%20metaphoric%20reference%20to%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2019%2F9%2F4%2Findia-revokes-kashmirs-special-status%5C%22%3Eunilateral%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202019%20to%20revoke%20Article%20370%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20that%20gave%20the%20region%20some%20degree%20of%20autonomy%20and%20the%20bifurcation%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20This%20decision%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20brutal%2C%20months-long%20communications%20lockdown%20in%20the%20region%20that%20Hoskote%20reimagines%20poetically%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20clapped%20his%20hands%20and%20blew%20on%20them%3Cbr%3E%5Cncould%20of%20chalk%20dust%20settled%20on%20our%20desks%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eburying%20them%20for%20years%20in%20snow%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20the%20image%20he%20chooses%20to%20express%20the%20aesthetics%20of%20poetry%20in%20this%20book%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I%20call%20%E2%80%9Cannihilation%20aesthetics%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20is%20light%20refracted%20through%20ice.%20There%20is%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20loss%20that%20shoots%20through%20the%20poems%2C%20many%20are%20dedicated%20to%20people%20who%20have%20died%20recently.%20The%20book%20is%20dedicated%20to%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20who%20died%20in%202021.%20At%20least%20three%20poems%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%9CAubade%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CBreath%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9CBed%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20were%20earlier%20published%20in%20an%20anthology%20on%20the%20pandemic%20and%20lockdown%2C%20edited%20by%20K.%20Satchidanandan%20and%20Nishi%20Chawla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20first%20poem%20expresses%20a%20desire%20to%20disappear%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20there%20was%20no%20border%3Cbr%3E%5Cnbetween%20flesh%20and%20light%3Cbr%3E%5CnWhat%20if%20I%20had%3Cbr%3E%5Cnno%20skin%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObjects%2C%20including%20human%20beings%2C%20can%20be%20seen%20because%20light%20reflects%20on%20them%3B%20turning%20transparent%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20also%20a%20process%20of%20turning%20invisible.%20This%20image%20sustains%20throughout%20the%20book%2C%20a%20light%20so%20refracted%20and%20otherworldly%20that%20it%20is%20difficult%20not%20to%20be%20blinded%20by%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20final%20poem%20of%20the%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9CReturn%E2%80%9D%2C%20Hoskote%20leaves%20us%20with%20a%20post-apocalyptic%20vision%20of%20the%20world.%20A%20ship%20abandoned%20in%20the%20clouds%2C%20without%20any%20captain%20or%20crew%20or%20compass%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eas%20you%20stumble%20towards%20the%20latched%20gate%3Cbr%3E%5Cnout-of-breath%20traveller%3Cbr%3E%5Cnstammering%20a%20word%20of%20thanks%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Elight%20returns%20to%20the%20world%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20this%20the%20light%20of%20a%20fadeout%20%E2%80%94%20a%20white%20darkness%20of%20sorts%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20film%20that%20leaves%20you%20gobsmacked%20(this%20book%20definitely%20does)%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20a%20metaphor%20for%20hope%2C%20of%20renewal%3F%20One%20must%20believe%20that%20it%20is%2C%20simply%20to%20carry%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUttaran%20Das%20Gupta%20is%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20writer%20and%20journalist.%20He%20teaches%20journalism%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20Sonipat.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701676841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04122322%2FRH-Icelight.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fverse-affairs-annihilation-aesthetics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ranjit%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20latest%20collection%20of%20poetry%C2%A0'Icelight'%C2%A0explores%20pandemic%20and%20global%20warming-induced%20annihilation%20anxiety%20but%20finds%20refuge%20in%20poetry%20and%20language.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fverse-affairs-annihilation-aesthetics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Shooting%20at%20home%20in%20Washington%20kills%205%20including%20suspect'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701676619000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105722993%2Cimgsize-87596.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fshooting-at-home-in-washington-state-kills-5-including-the-suspected-shooter-report-says%2Farticleshow%2F105722276.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105722276.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EFive%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20shooting%20at%20a%20Washington%20state%20home%20where%20police%20said%20the%20deceased%20included%20the%20suspected%20shooter%2C%20according%20to%20a%20news%20report.%20The%20Clark%20County%20Sheriff's%20Office%20said%20officers%20found%20the%20bodies%20inside%20a%20home%20in%20Orchards%2C%20Washington%2C%20following%20a%20call%20around%201pm%20Sunday%2C%20KGW8-TV%20reported.%20The%20sheriff's%20office%20said%20a%20family%20member%20received%20a%20text%20message%20from%20a%20person%20at%20the%20home%20saying%20they%20had%20harmed%20people%20there%2C%20KGW8%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fshooting-at-home-in-washington-state-kills-5-including-the-suspected-shooter-repo